snippet.textDisplay: I'm an ENFP and have really close Introverted friends, and they're not shy at all. This video makes it seem like introverts have some type of social anxiety, which is not true. My closest friend is an INTJ and when we're hanging out she is very bubbly, and has a lot to say, but on a day-to-day basis, she will PREFER to just observe and listen, and then give her perspective (confidently) if she feels the need, but otherwise she just prefers to reserve her energy for herself and the people she is close to. All this whispering made me lol
